A pirate, with a peg leg, a hook for a hand, and an eye patch, is sitting at a bar and a guy walks up and asks him how he lost his leg.  The pirate responds: ‚ÄúArrr I went into the swamps to bury me treasure and a damn crock attacked me from the bushes and bit me leg off before I could fight him off with me sword.‚Äù
The guy thinks this is a pretty entertaining story, so a couple rums later asks the pirate how he ended up with a hook for a hand.  To which the pirate responded: ‚ÄúI went back to get me treasure, but this time I thought I was ready for the crock so when I got close to me treasure and he jumped out to attack me I suck my sword down his throat and he bit me hand off!‚Äù
By this point the guy can‚Äôt wait to hear the next story so he asks the pirate if the crock took his eye too.  The pirate again responded: ‚ÄúI wish!  It was my first day with this here hook,‚Äù as he waved the hook in the mans face, ‚Äúand I was on my ship looking up at the clouds and a seagull shat in me eye!‚Äù
